1) Fix the damn logo visibility (now, not theory)

You’ve got two ready-to-ship options. Use both and never suffer the “invisible logo” again.

Option A: Auto-backplate only behind the logo

Drops a soft glow plate behind the PNG so it’s readable on any dark header without changing your site design.

html
<!-- In your header -->
<img class="logo" src="/assets/divergify_logo_transparent_5000.png" alt="Divergify">

css
/* Makes transparent PNG readable on dark backgrounds without a clunky box */
.logo {
  display: inline-block;
  position: relative;
  height: 72px; /* tweak if needed */
  filter: drop-shadow(0 0 6px rgba(255,255,255,0.9))
          drop-shadow(0 0 2px rgba(255,255,255,0.8));
}

/* If you’re using a true dark header, add a subtle plate */
header .logo {
  background: radial-gradient(closest-side, rgba(255,255,255,0.18), transparent 70%);
  border-radius: 14px;
  padding: 8px 12px;
}

Option B: Swap to the green logo on dark themes

Transparent for light, green for dark. Automatic, zero thinking.

html
<picture>
  <source media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)" srcset="/assets/divergify_logo_green_5000.png">
  <img class="logo" src="/assets/divergify_logo_transparent_5000.png" alt="Divergify">
</picture>

That combo makes the logo pop everywhere. If your site doesn’t use prefers-color-scheme, just add a .dark class to <html> or the header and switch the src with a one-liner.

Divergify — Mvp Feature Blueprint & Technical Architecture (beta-ready)

Divergify — MVP Feature Blueprint & Technical Architecture (Beta-ready)

Version: 0.1 (ship-ready blueprint) Owner: Takoda (engineering), You (vision, voice)

0) One-liner

A neurodivergent-first productivity companion that blends instant capture, mood-aware planning, sprint workflows, and a sarcastically loyal AI sidekick. Local-first, privacy-forward, deeply interactive.

1) Product pillars

  • Neuro-spicy by design: language and UX built from Divergipedia.

  • Local-first, sync-optional: works offline, syncs only when user opts in.

  • High interaction, low friction: voice capture, adaptive lists, gentle-but-firm nudges.

  • Dopamine-positive: micro wins, escalating rewards, never-punitive.

  • Tin Foil Hat Mode: zero analytics, reduced surface area, obvious visual state.

2) MVP scope (beta)

  1. Onboarding: choose sidekick voice + privacy level; seed Anchor Task; set nudge preferences.

  2. Home (Command Center): today’s Anchor Task, brain weather status, reward meter, quick capture.

  3. Spark Capture: instant voice/text capture → transcribe → quick-categorize to Idea Inbox or Task.

  4. Daily Check-in (Brain Weather): mood + energy sliders; optional notes; impacts task ordering.

  5. Tasks: sprintable tasks, tags (Anchor, Sprintable, Low-Spoons), priority orbit, due/estimate.

  6. Focus Sprint: configurable timer, distraction detector, end-of-sprint summary.

  7. Rewards: Micro Win Parade with escalating confetti/animations; copy rotation with 72h no-repeat.

  8. Sidekick Chat: AI companion with selectable persona; planning prompts; summarization; redirection.

  9. Settings: Tin Foil Hat, voice packs, themes, nudge intensity, data export/import.

  10. Sync (optional): Supabase auth + storage; encrypted at rest; user-controlled.

Out of scope for MVP: calendar sync, buddy mode, marketplace, complex routines builder. Parked for v1.1.

3) Personas & JTBD snapshots

  • Spark Jumper (ADHD-C): capture chaotic ideas fast, minimize context tax.

  • Overloaded Parent: quick planning, gentle nudges, privacy.

  • Late-night Maker: deep focus, low-UI noise, offline.

Key jobs:

  • “When my brain pops ideas, I need capture without friction so I don’t lose them.”

  • “When my spoons are low, I need tasks that match energy so I still win.”

  • “When I drift, I need a nudge that’s kind but firm.”

4) Screen map & primary flows

Screens

  1. Onboarding

  2. Home (Command Center)

  3. Spark Capture (Voice/Text)

  4. Brain Weather (Daily Check-in)

  5. Tasks (List + Detail)

  6. Focus Sprint (Timer)

  7. Sidekick Chat

  8. Settings

  9. Data & Sync (Export/Import, Account)

Core flows

  • Capture → Sort: Voice/Text → transcript → classify: Idea Inbox or Task → tag Sprintable.

  • Check-in → Plan: Mood/Energy → weights → reorder Tasks → suggest Anchor Task.

  • Sprint: choose Sprintable → run timer → detect drift → reward → log.

  • Chat Assist: ask planning help → sidekick proposes plan → one-tap create tasks.

  • Privacy: toggle Tin Foil → disable analytics, use local store only, UI changes state.

5) Visual & brand system

  • Base colors: Dark base #0b1217, Mint #dbffe3, Electric Green #2ECC71, Accent haze #9beab3.

  • Logo handling: transparent PNG on light; green logo on dark; auto backplate glow for readability.

  • Typography: Inter or Manrope; bold weights for headings; high contrast.

  • Motion: quick, playful, never overwhelming; haptics on rewards.

  • Copy: Divergipedia terms throughout (Anchor Task, Brain Weather, Spark Capture, etc.).

6) Data model (local-first → sync)

Entities

  • UserPrefs: theme, privacyMode, sidekickVoice, nudgeIntensity.

  • Checkin: id, ts, mood(−3..+3), energy(0..100), notes.

  • Task: id, title, notes, tags[], estimateMin, dueAt, createdAt, updatedAt, status(enum: open, done, archived), weights{effort, reward, energyFit}.

  • Sprint: id, taskId, startedAt, durationSec, completed, driftEvents[], notes.

  • RewardEvent: id, ts, type(task_done|sprint_done|streak), points, copyId.

  • Idea: id, content, source(voice|text), createdAt, linkedTaskId?

  • ChatMessage: id, role(user|assistant|system), content, ts, meta{persona, topic}.

Storage

  • Local: SQLite via Expo SQLite; secrets via SecureStore.

  • Sync: Supabase tables mirroring entities; RLS policies per user.

7) Algorithms

7.1 Energy-aware task ordering

score = w_priority + w_energyFit + w_recencyBoost - w_effortPenalty - w_contextSwitch
where:
energyFit = 1 - |task.energyDemand - user.energy|/100
recencyBoost = sigmoid(daysSinceCreated)

Weights tuned via config. In Tin Foil mode, all local.

7.2 Distraction/Drift detector

Heuristic signals during Sprint:

  • App backgrounded > N seconds.

  • Navigation away from Sprint screen.

  • Multiple rapid task switches. → Trigger gentle nudge: “Intentional Interrupt?”

7.3 Reward meter

  • Base points: task_done=10, sprint_done=15, streak_bonus=5×streakTier.

  • Tier animation: Tier 1 small confetti; Tier 2 graffiti burst; Tier 3 screen shimmer + haptic heavy.

  • Copy rotation: pool of ~120 messages, hashed by day + userId; 72h no-repeat via recent-history set.

8) AI sidekick

Personas (selectable)

  • Coach Snark: blunt, funny, corrective.

  • Soft Anchor: warm, reassuring.

  • Deadpan Analyst: structured, minimal.

Prompt scaffolding

  • System: brand voice rules + safety + brevity.

  • Context: today’s Anchor Task, Brain Weather, recent tasks, last chat turn.

  • Tools: can propose task lists, break tasks into Sprintables, generate summaries.

API interaction

  • Client calls our /chat endpoint with: messages[], persona, context bundle.

  • Server relays to LLM provider with guardrails; strips PII; returns text + suggested actions.

9) Security & privacy

  • Tin Foil Hat Mode: disables network calls except explicit sync/export; hides identifiers; local-only.

  • At rest: Supabase row-level security; local SQLite not encrypted by default → sensitive items mirrored in SecureStore or encrypted blobs.

  • In transit: TLS only.

  • PII minimization: no contacts/calendar access in MVP; no 3rd-party trackers.

  • Export/Import: JSON file to user-controlled storage.

  • Content moderation: server-side safety filters for chat.

10) Tech stack

  • Mobile: React Native (Expo SDK 51), React Navigation.

  • Voice: react-native-voice (Android+iOS), Expo AV.

  • Transcription: client-side recording → server transcription endpoint.

  • Backend: Supabase (Postgres, Auth, Storage, RLS).

  • API: Node/Express or Fastify; tRPC optional; deploy on Fly.io/Render.

  • Notifications: Expo Notifications.

  • State: Zustand or Redux Toolkit; React Query for server-state.

11) API spec (initial)

POST /auth/register → {token} POST /auth/login → {token} GET /me → profile, prefs GET /tasks / POST /tasks / PATCH /tasks/:id GET /checkins / POST /checkins POST /sprints (start/stop) POST /rewards/event POST /ideas POST /chat → {assistant, suggestions[{type, payload}]}

Auth: Bearer JWT from Supabase.

12) Navigation & components

  • Stacks: OnboardingStack, MainTabs(Home, Tasks, Sprint, Chat, Settings).

  • Key components: LogoHeader, RewardMeter, EnergySliders, TaskCard, VoiceButton, NudgeToast.

14) Acceptance criteria (MVP)

  • Onboarding lets user pick persona and privacy mode; persists across relaunch.

  • Capture records voice, produces transcript, saves Idea or Task in <10s on average connection.

  • Daily Check-in changes task ordering by energy.

  • Sprint timer runs reliably in background for ≥30 minutes.

  • Rewards animate at 3 tiers; copy does not repeat inside 72h window.

  • Tin Foil Hat prevents any network call except explicit export/import.

  • Chat produces actionable steps and can create tasks with one tap.

  • Full app usable offline (except chat/transcription); no crashes for 24h soak test.

15) Implementation plan (by sprint)

Sprint A: State store, theme, navigation, Home scaffold, Tasks crud (local), Check-in UI. Sprint B: Sprint timer w/ drift heuristic, Reward meter tier 1–3, copy rotation store. Sprint C: Voice capture + transcription endpoint (server stub), Idea Inbox, convert-to-task. Sprint D: AI chat endpoint + client screen, suggested actions → tasks pipeline. Sprint E: Supabase sync, auth, export/import to file; Tin Foil mode gating. Sprint F: Polish, QA, accessibility pass, store assets, beta builds.

16) QA checklist

  • Offline mode for every screen.

  • Airplane mode during capture → retry path.

  • App termination mid-sprint → recover session.

  • Notifications delivered cross-platform.

  • 72h reward-copy window upheld (unit tests around copy history).

  • RLS policies deny cross-user reads/writes.

17) Copy: reward lines (sample pool)

  • “Neurons did a high five.”

18) Server sketch (pseudo-code)

// rewards.ts
export function pickRewardCopy(userId: string, pool: string[], history: string[]): string {
const now = Date.now();
const recent = new Set(history.filter(h => now - parseInt(h.split(':')[0],10) < 72*3600*1000).map(h => h.split(':')[1]));
const candidates = pool.filter(x => !recent.has(x));
const pick = candidates[Math.floor((hash(userId+now.toString())%candidates.length))] || pool[0];
return pick;
}

23) Supabase schema (DDL sketch)

create table users (
id uuid primary key,
created_at timestamptz default now()
);

create table prefs (
user_id uuid primary key references users(id) on delete cascade,
persona text,
privacy_mode boolean default false,
nudge_intensity int default 1
);

create table tasks (
id uuid primary key,
user_id uuid references users(id) on delete cascade,
title text not null,
notes text,
tags text[],
estimate_min int,
due_at timestamptz,
status text check (status in ('open','done','archived')) default 'open',
weights jsonb,
created_at timestamptz default now(),
updated_at timestamptz default now()
);

create table checkins (
id uuid primary key,
user_id uuid references users(id) on delete cascade,
mood int,
energy int,
notes text,
created_at timestamptz default now()
);

-- RLS example
alter table tasks enable row level security;
create policy "own-tasks" on tasks for all
using (auth.uid() = user_id) with check (auth.uid() = user_id);
